
Comment: The experiment was carried out at a Van de Graaff and a Tandem accelerators and the target 
	 was a thin film of Al evaporated onto a thin film of Ag. The listed uncertainties in the 
	 cross-section values are statistical and also due to peak area determination. There is a 
	 systematic uncertainty of 7% (see Sigma scale factor fields). As the gamma-ray line is 
	 isotropic total cross section values may be obtained by multiplying by 4pi.			
			
